## Absolute Rules
1. Never delete or modify existing tests in tests/
2. If a test fails, fix the code — not the test
3. Treat docs/plans.md active milestone as the scope boundary
4. Update only .forge/state/current/queue.json task statuses — never open the next milestone yourself
5. Run ./forge qa before finishing a session, and repair failures before exit
6. Do NOT run git commit — checkpointing handles session commits
7. Append durable discoveries to docs/backlog.md instead of expanding scope mid-run
8. If a run was interrupted, resume via ./forge run --resume instead of opening a fresh milestone
{{ADDITIONAL_RULES}}

## Session Start Protocol
1. Run: ./forge status
2. Read output to understand current state
3. Read docs/prompt.md, docs/plans.md, docs/implement.md, docs/documentation.md
4. Pick the first available pending task from .forge/state/current/queue.json
5. Implement, validate, and update queue status
6. Add a short note under docs/documentation.md Session Notes

